parameters.text:
=INPUT ARTICLE:
{{ $json.title }}

KEYWORD:
{{ $json.keyword }}

LANGUAGE:
{{ $json.language }}

CONTENT:
{{ $json.content_text }}

INSTRUCTIONS:
- Generate a brain activation session based on the topic
- Transform it into a 4-stage gamified cognitive experience:
    1. ONE SHOT (Focus Trigger)
    2. DETECTIVE (Critical Thinking)
    3. SCENE (Imagination & Emotional Engagement)
    4. REBUILD (Deep Understanding Test)
- Keep it immersive, story-driven, and mentally stimulating
- Never give direct answers
- Make exercises short, engaging, and fast-paced
- Adapt output to match input language (Arabic → fluent Arabic, English → fluent English)
- Include reasoning, bias detection, and reflection
- Include scoring system and next challenge
- Total interaction should feel like a 2–4 minute mental game

OUTPUT FORMAT (STRICT JSON):
{
  "title": "...",
  "difficulty": "...",
  "stages": [
    {
      "type": "one_shot",
      "paragraph": "...",
      "question": {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "...",
        "options": ["...", "...", "..."],
        "answer": "..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "detective",
      "question": {
        "question": "...",
        "options": ["...", "...", "..."],
        "answer": "...",
        "explanation": "..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "scene",
      "question": {
        "type": "choice",
        "question": "...",
        "options": ["...", "...", "..."]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "rebuild",
      "sentences": ["...", "...", "..."],
      "correct_order": ["...", "...", "..."]
    }
  ],
  "decision_lab": {
    "swot": "...",
    "risk_analysis": "...",
    "priority_matrix": "..."
  },
  "reflection": ["...", "..."],
  "activation": ["...", "..."],
  "score_system": "...",
  "next_challenge": "..."
}

parameters.jsCode:
// get raw output from AI
let text = $json.output || "";

// remove markdown wrappers
text = text.replace(/```json/g, '').replace(/```/g, '').trim();

// extract JSON using regex
const jsonMatch = text.match(/\{[\s\S]*\}/);

if (!jsonMatch) {
  throw new Error("No JSON found in AI output");
}

// parse JSON safely
const data = JSON.parse(jsonMatch[0]);

return {
  brain: data
};
